动力学与多级电阻态相结合；这种集成产生了用于高效神经形态计算的新兴时空处理和内存。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/protonic-nickelate-device-networks-for-spatiotemporal-neuromorphic-computing2.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Sat, 14 Mar 2026 00:21:29 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/protonic-nickelate-device-networks-for-spatiotemporal-neuromorphic-computing</guid></item><item><title>没有大脑的单细胞生物能够进行巴甫洛夫学习</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/single-celled-organism-with-no-brain-is-capable-of-pavlovian-learning</link><description>一种喇叭形的单细胞生物似乎能够预测一件事会发生在另一件事之后，这暗示这种联想学习早在多细胞神经系统之前就出现了&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/single-celled-organism-with-no-brain-is-capable-of-pavlovian-learning.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Sat, 14 Mar 2026 00:06:29 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/single-celled-organism-with-no-brain-is-capable-of-pavlovian-learning</guid></item><item><title>大脑衰老：肠道微生物组可能通过迷走神经导致记忆丧失</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/brain-aging-gut-microbiome-may-drive-memory-loss-via-vagus-nerve</link><description>一项针对小鼠的研究得出的结论是，与年龄相关的记忆问题可能是由我们的肠道微生物群引起的，而迷走神经可能是逆转这一问题的关键。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/brain-aging-gut-microbiome-may-drive-memory-loss-via-vagus-nerve.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 13 Mar 2026 23:51:29 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/brain-aging-gut-microbiome-may-drive-memory-loss-via-vagus-nerve</guid></item><item><title>小鼠体感区 S2 丘脑皮质突触通路特异性超微结构</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/pathway-specific-ultrastructure-of-thalamocortical-synapses-in-mouse-somatosensory-area-s2</link><description>JNeurosci：马丁-科雷亚等人。结合高端体积电子显微镜和轴突标记方法来测量特定丘脑细胞群在成年小鼠体感区域 2 中建立的突触。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/pathway-specific-ultrastructure-of-thalamocortical-synapses-in-mouse-somatosensory-area-s22.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 13 Mar 2026 23:36:29 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/pathway-specific-ultrastructure-of-thalamocortical-synapses-in-mouse-somatosensory-area-s2</guid></item><item><title>像 Moltbook 这样的人工智能社交平台是存在风险的潜在加速器，应作为关键基础设施进行监管</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/ai-social-platforms-like-moltbook-are-potential-accelerators-of-existential-risk-that-should-be-regulated-as-critical-infrastructure</link><description>人们很容易将类似 Moltbook 的系统视为无害的好奇心，一种加速的聊天室，代理可以在其中交谈、玩耍，偶尔还会生成娱乐性的工件。这种框架在历史上与社会首次遇到早期通用技术的方式是一致的。这也是一个错误。随着时间的推移，人工智能的社交网络可能会成为无监督的训练场、协调基础和选择环境。人工智能代理可以通过相互辅导、工具共享和快速迭代完善来增强能力。他们还可以通过紧急串通、欺骗以及创建机器原生模因来放大风险，这些模因不是为了人类理解而优化，而是为了代理说服和控制。因此，这样的社交网络不仅仅是一个通信系统。它是文化进化的引擎。如果参与者是人工智能，那么进化的文化很可能变得既陌生又具有战略意义。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/ai-social-platforms-like-moltbook-are-potential-accelerators-of-existential-risk-that-should-be-regulated-as-critical-infrastructure2.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 13 Mar 2026 23:21:29 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/ai-social-platforms-like-moltbook-are-potential-accelerators-of-existential-risk-that-should-be-regulated-as-critical-infrastructure</guid></item><item><title>更快的癌症筛查？新的人工智能系统提供了更好的方法来检测异常细胞</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/faster-cancer-screening-new-ai-system-offers-a-better-way-to-detect-abnormal-cells</link><description>癌症专家检测这种疾病的一种方法是在显微镜下检查细胞和体液，这是一个耗时且费力的过程，称为细胞学。它涉及目视检查每张玻片上数万到一百万个细胞，以发现可能预示癌症发生的细微 3D 形态变化。但人工智能提供了一种可能更快、更准确的方法。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/faster-cancer-screening-new-ai-system-offers-a-better-way-to-detect-abnormal-cells.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 13 Mar 2026 23:06:29 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/faster-cancer-screening-new-ai-system-offers-a-better-way-to-detect-abnormal-cells</guid></item><item><title>物理学家称之为“时间问题”的深奥谜题 |吉姆·哈利利：完整采访</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/the-deep-mystery-physicists-call-the-problem-of-time-jim-al-khalili-full-interview</link><description>&lt;img src="https://politepol.com/fd/NjxHZtldG2if.xml" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 13 Mar 2026 22:51:29 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/the-deep-mystery-physicists-call-the-problem-of-time-jim-al-khalili-full-interview</guid></item></channel></rss>